SIMPLE: bristol
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bristol
<hw>Bris"tol</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A seaport city in
the west of England.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Bristol board</b></col>, <cd>a kind of fine pasteboard,
made with a smooth but usually unglazed surface.</cd> -- <col><b>Bristol
brick</b></col>, <cd>a brick of siliceous matter used for polishing
cultery; -- originally manufactured at <ets>Bristol</ets>.</cd> --
<col><b>Bristol stone</b></col>, <cd>rock crystal, or brilliant crystals
of quartz, found in the mountain limestone near <ets>Bristol</ets>, and
used in making ornaments, vases, etc. When polished, it is called
<stype>Bristol diamond</stype>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brisure</ent>⟦br⟧
